SUMMARY:Friday Under the Stars
DESCRIPTION:Come join us for our astronomical series: Friday Under the Stars!\nRaleigh Astronomy Club will be hosting a monthly night sky viewing session at one of our private sites that will only be open for this event. The old site for Three Bears Acres will be the perfect location for star viewing fun so bring a blanket or chair and we will see you there!\n\nBecause this is a private preserve\, we ask that you leave furry friends at home. The event address will also be sent in your confirmation email. We suggest that you bring a picnic blanket or chair to stargaze in\, a red flashlight\, and snacks and a water bottle. Please remember to pack anything that you bring in\, back out with you and we can’t wait to see you amongst the stars! This is a free event\, but preregistration is required. Make sure to save your spot below!\n\n\n\n \n\nIf registration is full\, please fill out the waitlist form here by April 2nd at noon.\n\n 
URL:https://triangleland.org/event/friday-under-the-stars-3
LOCATION:Three Bears (Private Preserve)\, Creedmoor\, NC\, 27522\, United States
ORGANIZER;CN="Amaya Horner":MAILTO:ahorner@triangleland.org
END:VEVENT
